\vspace{0.5cm}

\textbf{Re: Software Engineering Internship – 5G Software R\&D}

\vspace{0.5cm}

Dear Hiring Team,

\vspace{0.3cm}

I am writing to apply for the 2026 Software Engineering Internship within the 5G Software R\&D team at Keysight Technologies. As Physics teacher with strong programming experience and a keen interest in telecommunications systems, I am motivated to contribute to the development, integration and testing of next-generation software platforms and protocols.

My academic projects have required full lifecycle software development, including design, implementation, validation and technical documentation. In my quantum computing project, I developed modular Python applications to interact with cloud-based hardware systems, processed structured data outputs, and performed systematic validation and debugging to ensure reliability. These experiences strengthened my understanding of integration, verification and structured software engineering practices.

Additionally, my embedded systems project involved implementing C++ control algorithms, integrating hardware and software components, and performing iterative testing to achieve stable performance. I am comfortable working with structured data formats such as JSON and XML, and I have foundational knowledge of SQL and networking concepts relevant to communication systems.

I am particularly drawn to Keysight’s leadership in 5G and advanced communications technologies. The opportunity to work within an experienced development team, contribute to commercially impactful solutions, and gain exposure to modern development tools strongly aligns with my career goals in software engineering and high-performance systems.

I am a proactive and technically curious individual who enjoys solving complex engineering challenges and working collaboratively within a team environment. I would welcome the opportunity to contribute to Keysight’s continued innovation.

Thank you for your time and consideration. I look forward to the opportunity to discuss my application further.

\vspace{0.5cm}

Sincerely, \\
\vspace{0.2cm}
Zaher Faruk

